The five highest demand majors include: Psychology, Economics, Biology, Computer Science and Computer Engineering. Many students choose to join the UC Santa Cruz community because of the distinctive opportunities to take part in undergraduate research and scholarship; six in 10 students participate in research projects before their graduation, a demonstration of the campus’ strong commitment to transformative undergraduate education.
Among the 74 percent of frosh who indicated a major, their distribution is:
● 32 percent Physical & Biological Sciences, including Biology;
● 29 percent Social Sciences, including Psychology and Economics;
● 27 percent Engineering, including Computer Science and Computer Engineering;
● 7 percent Humanities, with the highest demand in Literature;
● 5 percent Arts, with the highest demand major in Film & Digital Media.
